body.name: MSI Gaming AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT MECH 2X 8G OC 128-bit 8GB GDDR6 DP/HDMI Dual Torx Fans FreeSync DirectX 12 VR Ready OC Computer Gaming Graphics Card, AMD GPU Video Cards for Gaming PC (Renewed)
features: Powerful Performance: The MSI Gaming AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT MECH 2X 8G OC is equipped with the AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT GPU architecture, providing excellent graphics performance for gaming enthusiasts. Its 8GB GDDR6 video memory and 128-bit memory interface ensure smooth gameplay and efficient data transfer.

Dual Torx Fans for Effective Cooling: With dual Torx fans, this graphics card effectively dissipates heat and maintains optimal temperatures during intense gaming sessions. The fans operate quietly while keeping the GPU cool, ensuring reliable and consistent performance.

Versatile Display Connectivity: The card supports DisplayPort and HDMI outputs, allowing you to connect multiple displays or high-resolution monitors for an immersive gaming experience or enhanced productivity. You can enjoy stunning visuals and smooth gameplay on your preferred setup.

FreeSync Technology for Tear-Free Gaming: Featuring AMD's FreeSync technology, the RX 6600 XT MECH 2X 8G OC synchronizes the display's refresh rate with the GPU's frame rate, reducing screen tearing and delivering a seamless gaming experience. You can enjoy fluid visuals and enhanced responsiveness in your favorite games.

Overclocking Capabilities and VR Ready: The graphics card is designed with overclocking capabilities, allowing you to push its performance to even higher levels. By increasing the clock speeds of the GPU and memory, you can achieve higher frame rates and smoother gaming experiences. Additionally, it is VR ready, ensuring compatibility with virtual reality applications for an immersive gaming experience.
body.description: ''The MSI Gaming AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT MECH 2X 8G OC is a high-performance graphics card designed for gaming enthusiasts and PC enthusiasts who demand excellent graphics performance. This graphics card is based on the AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT GPU architecture, which delivers exceptional visuals and smooth gameplay. The card features 8GB of GDDR6 video memory, providing ample room for rendering high-resolution textures and handling graphically demanding games. With its 128-bit memory interface, it ensures fast and efficient data transfer between the GPU and memory, resulting in improved overall performance. To maintain optimal temperatures and prevent overheating during intense gaming sessions, the MSI Gaming RX 6600 XT MECH 2X 8G OC is equipped with dual Torx fans. These fans operate quietly while effectively dissipating heat from the GPU, ensuring reliable and consistent performance. The graphics card supports DisplayPort and HDMI outputs, allowing you to connect multiple displays or high-resolution monitors for an immersive gaming experience or enhanced productivity. It also supports AMD's FreeSync technology, which synchronizes the display's refresh rate with the GPU's frame rate, reducing screen tearing and providing smoother gameplay.''',

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you buy this card. Add support to it right after installing it!
reviews.reviewText: don't get me wrong. So far it's been a great card. really quiet and performs great. I switched to it from a nvidia card so I had to use DDU to uninstall my previous drivers, But however I cannot emphasize enough! add a support bracket to this card right after putting it into your computer or you may end up with a bent pcb. this card is only fully supported by it's pcb after being screwed into a pcie express slot on the case. heavy gaming may increase heat to 59-60 degrees. enough to soften the pcb and cause bending under the weight of the heatsink. it's only supported by the pcb and whatever the pcie slot on your motherboard has to offer. you can see it from the pictures advertised. there's a bare space between the fan shroud where the card mounts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It does what it says on the tin
reviews.reviewText: The card showed up quickly and installed just as fast. I had some hesitation due to the card being refurbished, but it may as well be brand new with the way it performs. This is a great card for a 1080p rig and is as quiet as other reviews on the net say. I mainly bought this for playing games like The Witcher 3 and Cyberpunk 2077, the card knocks it out of the park with high frame rates on ultra+ settings but does struggle with RT enabled. I wouldn’t knock off points for that seeing as this was a well known issue with this gen of card so it was to be expected. All in all it does exactly what I need it to and stays dead quiet while doing it.
